The following parts of this product are derived from etcd-io/raft and
translated from Go to MoonBit:

  * The Raft protocol core: leader election, log replication, log matching
    and commit rules, the per-follower Progress state machine, snapshotting
    and log compaction, joint-consensus membership change, read-index and
    leader-lease linearizable reads, and leadership transfer.
  * The storage engine model (an etcd-style in-memory storage with
    index/term/slice reads, conflict-truncating append, compaction and
    snapshotting) and the HardState persistence model.
  * The test suite, ported from the Go tests of etcd-io/raft, including the
    Raft paper conformance tests.

Modifications and additions made in this product:

  * Reimplemented in the MoonBit language, with the data model expressed
    through algebraic data types and exhaustive pattern matching rather than
    Go structs and switch statements.
  * Added a deterministic simulation harness with a single-seed discrete-time
    network able to drop, delay, reorder and partition messages and to crash
    and restart nodes, together with built-in safety-invariant checks
    (election safety, an agreeing committed prefix, and log matching).
  * Added a browser demo that compiles the consensus core to WebAssembly and
    runs each node in its own Web Worker.

